# AGNOS Code Owners
#
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# Owners are automatically requested for review when someone opens a PR
# that modifies code matching a pattern.
#
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: AGNOS core team owns everything
*                           @agnos/core-team

# Kernel code — kernel experts only
/kernel/                    @agnos/kernel-team

# Security-critical code — security team required
/userland/agnos-sys/        @agnos/security-team @agnos/core-team
/docs/security/             @agnos/security-team
/userland/agnos-common/src/security.rs  @agnos/security-team
/userland/agnos-common/src/audit.rs     @agnos/security-team
/userland/agent-runtime/src/sandbox.rs  @agnos/security-team

# LLM Gateway — AI/ML team
/userland/llm-gateway/      @agnos/ai-team @agnos/core-team

# Desktop environment
/userland/desktop-environment/  @agnos/desktop-team

# CI/CD changes require DevOps review
/.github/                   @agnos/devops-team @agnos/core-team

# Documentation
/docs/                      @agnos/core-team
/README.md                  @agnos/core-team
/CHANGELOG.md               @agnos/core-team

# Legal / compliance files — requires legal/leadership review
/LICENSE                    @agnos/core-team
/SECURITY.md                @agnos/security-team @agnos/core-team
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md         @agnos/core-team
